Tornado plot showing the impact of variable parameters on the postharvest output, i.e., the median predicted annual number of E. coli O157:H7 (ECO157) illness cases. The spearman rank-order correlation coefficients (SRCC) are shown next to each parameter bar. Only variables statistically significant after the Bonferroni correction and with a correlation coefficient > 0.05 are shown. Positive values indicate positive correlation (i.e., an increase in a given parameter increases the number of illness cases), while negative values indicate negative correlation (i.e., an increase in a given parameter decreases the number of illness cases).

